Defendant Adisa M Reed in court with attorney Maayan Silver.  Defendant Adisa M Reed in custody.  Denis Stingl appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Additional statements by:  Ms. Brenda R. and Ms. Wynique R.     The Court imposed the following sentence:

AS TO COUNT 01:
Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be 5 years consecutive to any other sentence.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for 2 years 6 months.  Defendant shall serve 2 years 6 months on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.  The defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program, but not for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  The Court advised the defendant of his determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant.  The Court STAYED THE SENTENCE and placed the defendant on probation to the State Department of Corrections for a period of three (3) years.

 * Court ordered defendant to provide a DNA sample.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION (and Extended Supervision, if revoked):
 - No contact with the victim, Ms. Brenda R.,whatsoever, in person by phone or by third parties;
 - No contact with the Mount Mary College located at 2900 North Menomonee River Parkway, city of Glendale, county of Milwaukee, Wisconsin;
 - No controlled substances or alcohol;
 - Urine screens;
 - AODA assessment; treatment if needed;
 - Cognitive thinking intervention counseling;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Be given job and vocational training;
 - Anger management counseling;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Be given job and vocational training;
 - Undergo a mental health evaluation; follow thru with any treatment recommended;
 - Serve 6 months condition time at the House of Correction, with good time and release to Day Reporting Center;
 - Serve 30 days condition time for contempt of court; NO good time, however, release for Day Reporting Center allowed;
 - Pay DNA surcharge, costs, disbursements and supervision fees, including the costs and surcharges ordered in Count 2.  Should defendant get revoked, Court ordered monies taken from prison funds not to exceed 25%.  Balance to be paid while on extended supervision.

AS TO COUNT 02:
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 9 months at the House of Correction, with credit for 213 days; TIME SERVED DISPOSITION.
  - Pay the DNA surcharge, plus costs, while on probation/prison in Count 1.  

